{"key":"processedPost-10948247","value":{"id":10948247,"first":10947605,"last":10951884,"when":1251399660,"utime":"08/27/09 10:01 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />Should I hydrate those before adding with the coir, mix, then hydrate as needed?</blockquote><br />I prefer to mix everything and then hydrate.&nbsp; When it's at field capacity, a handful squeezed gently shouldn't drip, but if squeezed harder will spill a few drops, and if squeezed very hard will produce a small stream for a second or two and then stop.&nbsp; This is the moisture level you're looking for.&nbsp; Be sure to let it sit for ten minutes and test again.&nbsp; Often, you'll need to add more water as the substrate continues to absorb.&nbsp; After you get the correct moisture content, jar or bag it up and pasteurize at 140F to 160F(60C to 70C), measured at the center of the substrate, for 60 to 90 minutes.<br />RR","title":"Re: Such a thing as too much gypsum in sub.?"}}